{
  "doc_id": "6142",
  "text": "Solubility of pure drug and all batches of nanoparticles in distilled water were obtained by adding an excess amount of the pure drug and nanoparticles in 10 ml of distilled water in conical flask to saturated solution. This conical flask was kept on orbital shaker for 24 h to ensure saturation. After attaining the equilibrium solubility, clear supernatant was filtered, appropriately diluted and analysed spectrophotometrically by UV/Vis spectrophotometer at 248 nm [CITATION_1] .",
